31:28.240 --> 31:32.680
It can be, you know, service dogs can be blind people obviously, it can be autistic children

31:32.680 --> 31:33.840
often get them.

31:33.840 --> 31:38.080
It's just complete absolute devotion and what they call over and over again you hear of

31:38.080 --> 31:40.800
unconditional love.

31:40.800 --> 31:45.040
And how powerful the unconditional love is in the veteran community is because a lot

31:45.040 --> 31:50.200
of veterans have moral injury as they call it today and they have a lot of guilt and

31:50.200 --> 31:54.840
shame which are two powerful things because they've both, they've been commanded to as

31:54.840 --> 31:59.720
19 year olds to do things that are morally reprehensible or they've seen things that

31:59.720 --> 32:04.280
are so awful that they're embarrassed and they're shamed and they're guilty or because

32:04.280 --> 32:09.320
their mates have died and what runs through their mind is what they could have done to

32:09.320 --> 32:11.800
save them for the next 30 years.

32:11.800 --> 32:16.160
So they are so filled with shame that they can't release it and they end up off in a

32:16.160 --> 32:20.640
shut-ins and all over the country there's hundreds of thousands of veterans who are shut-ins

32:20.640 --> 32:25.320
and they get a dog, a service dog and the dog has to go out.

32:25.320 --> 32:30.640
So the first step is he has to take responsibility for the dog and take the dog out and he learns

32:30.640 --> 32:36.040
very quickly that no matter what he does even if he's weeping, even if he's crying, even

32:36.040 --> 32:42.120
if he's having a nightmare, if he's just sullen, the dog will love him and the dog will lick

32:42.120 --> 32:47.760
him and wake him up from nightmares and be his companion and so gradually he lets go

32:47.760 --> 32:49.720
and starts to love the dog.

32:49.720 --> 32:53.920
It seems to be pretty consistent and it's the first time he's felt anything in a long

32:53.920 --> 32:54.920
time.

