33:41.040 --> 33:45.440
One of the things that happens in a lot of psychiatric illnesses and certainly PTSD is

33:45.440 --> 33:54.040
among them and I'm not sure if people generally appreciate this very much but it's that caregivers

33:54.040 --> 33:58.840
get rebuffed off and I mean there are efforts to sort of cheer you up or encourage you or

33:58.840 --> 34:03.280
it gets you to do something like get outside or get out of bed.

34:03.280 --> 34:08.800
You're met with a lot of pushback that could be in various forms and we might imagine some

34:08.800 --> 34:13.280
with PTSD could be irritable but there's all sorts of ways people can push back and their

34:13.280 --> 34:19.880
psychiatric illness keeps them from responding to normal social cues and the failure of those

34:19.880 --> 34:25.440
social cues often demoralizes the caregivers so the caregivers give up to some degree in

34:25.440 --> 34:29.960
withdrawal and they start to dismiss the sufferer.

34:29.960 --> 34:35.160
So a dog or another animal who's trained in this way just keeps it up.

34:35.160 --> 34:40.720
